\,\rm c^{2J}\!+1\equiv 2\pmod{c+1}.\,
\rm\,\ \color{#c00}{c=2^{\large 2^{N}}}\!,\ \, 2J\, =\, 2^{K} \Rightarrow\ \color{#0a0}{c^{\large 2J}} = (2^{\large 2^{N}})^{\large 2^K}\!\! = \color{#0a0}{2^{\large 2^{N+K}}}\! 
\Rightarrow
